<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="csrf-token" content={get_csrf_token()} />
    <.live_title>
      {assigns[:page_title] || "Pinchflat"}
    </.live_title>
    <link phx-track-static rel="stylesheet" href={~p"/assets/app.css"} />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href={~p"/favicon.ico?cachebust=2024-03-20"} />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href={~p"/apple-touch-icon.png"} />
    <script defer phx-track-static type="text/javascript" src={~p"/assets/app.js"}>
    </script>
  </head>
  <body
    x-data={"{ 
      sidebarVisible: false,
      proEnabled: #{Settings.get!(:pro_enabled)},
      onboarding: #{Settings.get!(:onboarding)}
    }"}
    class="dark text-bodydark bg-boxdark-2"
    data-socket-path={Path.join(Application.get_env(:pinchflat, :base_route_path), "/live")}
  >
    {@inner_content}

    <.donate_modal conn={@conn} />
    <%!--
      Rendered unconditionally (NOT inside an `x-if`) so its nested LiveView
      (`UpgradeButtonLive`) exists in the DOM when `liveSocket.connect()` scans
      for views to join. Gating it behind Alpine's `x-if` meant the modal was
      cloned into the DOM after connect on some environments, so the nested
      LiveView never joined — leaving the "Unlock Pro" button permanently
      disabled (issue #125). Visibility is handled by show_modal/hide_modal; the
      pro triggers only open it while `!proEnabled && !onboarding`.
    --%>
    <.upgrade_modal conn={@conn} />
  </body>
</html>
